<paragraph blockId="19.[136,1452,950,1445]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis box="[136,200,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[214,472,1382,1408]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="thailandica">
<emphasis box="[214,472,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Roussoella thailandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed a sister group with 
<taxonomicName box="[779,897,1382,1408]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Roussoellaceae" genus="Roussoella" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="nitidula">
<emphasis box="[779,897,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">R. nitidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having smaller asci and ascospores (asci 95−120 × 7−9 µm vs. 110–200 × 8–11 μm; ascospores 13.5−15.5 ×4.5−6 µm vs. 16–19 × 5.5–7 μm).
</paragraph>
